Raspadskaya Shares Drop Most in 2 Weeks After Mechel Report

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-03-29T15:25:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/raspadskaya-shares-drop-to-lowest-in-week-after-mechel-report.html
OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP) ’s shares fell the
most in two weeks after RIA Novosti reported OAO Mechel is
seeking to buy the coal company at a price three times lower
than its shareholders expected.  Raspadskaya’s shares slid 3 percent to 191.26 rubles by the
6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, the biggest decline since March 15.  Mechel is prepared to pay no more than $2.3 billion, RIA
reported late yesterday, citing unidentified sources, while
Raspadskaya’s shareholders put the company’s value at $6
billion, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in London at 
